  "module1": {
    "clean_text": "A [AGE] female newborn was brought to our hospital following an abnormal screening result. She was born at full-term with a birth weight of 4380 grams. The parents reported no issues with feeding, activity levels, or crying strength. Newborn screening was conducted on her third day of life. On Day 4, the laboratory received her sample. By Day 6, results indicated a high-risk condition with GAA activity measured at 0.18 uM/h (critical cutoff < 0.5) and a ratio of 42.87 (critical cutoff acid β-glucosidase (ABG)/GAA ≥ 20). An urgent visit was arranged for Day 7. Upon examination, the newborn exhibited normal muscle power, normal reflexes, no macroglossia, but a slight decrease in facial folds.",
